Collapse runs iteratively. In each pass, any node (spec or marker) whose every touching edge is checked gets its baseline hash updated to the current scan hash. When a node's scan hash is empty string (deleted), the node is removed from the result and its edges are filtered out. Passes repeat until no node collapses. After all passes complete, resolutions touching collapsed nodes are pruned: deleted nodes get all resolutions pruned unconditionally; non-deleted collapsed nodes get resolutions pruned when the other endpoint is also in sync. This enables progressive collapse across many-to-many edge topologies. See principles.specs_are_truth.